  21 Feb 2011; Amadeusz Żołnowski <aidecoe@gentoo.org> plymouth-9999.ebuild,
  -files/gentoo_ply.png:
  I have moved gentoo-logo.png from 'files' to my web space on dev.gentoo.org
  and updated postinst message with warning about interactive feature of init
  system.

  21 Feb 2011; Amadeusz Żołnowski <aidecoe@gentoo.org>
  -files/0.8.3-drm-reduce-minimum-build-requirements.patch,
  -files/0.8.3-gentoo-fb-path.patch, -plymouth-0.8.3-r5.ebuild,
  -files/0.8.3-image-replace-deprecated-libpng-function.patch:
  Removed 0.8.3 ebuild as it's already committed into Portage tree.

  04 Feb 2011; Amadeusz Żołnowski <aidecoe@aidecoe.name>
  plymouth-0.8.3-r5.ebuild, plymouth-9999.ebuild:
  Lacked 'die' for ins commands.

  04 Feb 2011; Amadeusz Żołnowski <aidecoe@aidecoe.name>
  plymouth-0.8.3-r5.ebuild, plymouth-9999.ebuild:
  Added link in postinst message to instructions on how to setup Plymouth.

  04 Feb 2011; Amadeusz Żołnowski <aidecoe@aidecoe.name>
  -plymouth-0.8.3-r3.ebuild:
  Removed obsolete revision.

*plymouth-0.8.3-r5 (04 Feb 2011)

  04 Feb 2011; Amadeusz Żołnowski <aidecoe@aidecoe.name>
  -plymouth-0.8.3-r4.ebuild, +plymouth-0.8.3-r5.ebuild:
  Revision bump related to missing dracut dependency.

  04 Feb 2011; Amadeusz Żołnowski <aidecoe@aidecoe.name>
  plymouth-0.8.3-r4.ebuild, plymouth-9999.ebuild:
  plymouth initramfs generation scripts requires dracut-functions, therefore
  >=sys-kernel/dracut-007 dependency is needed.

*plymouth-9999 (04 Feb 2011)

  04 Feb 2011; Amadeusz Żołnowski <aidecoe@aidecoe.name>
  +files/9999-gentoo-fb-path.patch, plymouth-0.8.3-r4.ebuild,
  +plymouth-9999.ebuild, metadata.xml:
  9999: Live ebuild imported from bug #274065 (attachment #261479 by Lucian
  Muresan) and stripped from conditions to be git-only and simpler.

  0.8.3-r4: Using PATCHES array instead of manually specifying epatch commands.

  metdata.xml: Better flags' descriptions and package's long description.

*plymouth-0.8.3-r4 (03 Feb 2011)

  03 Feb 2011; Amadeusz Żołnowski <aidecoe@aidecoe.name>
  +files/0.8.3-drm-reduce-minimum-build-requirements.patch,
  +files/0.8.3-gentoo-fb-path.patch,
  +files/0.8.3-image-replace-deprecated-libpng-function.patch,
  +files/gentoo_ply.png, +files/plymouth.initd, -files/0.8.3-gentoo-fb.patch,
  plymouth-0.8.3-r3.ebuild, +plymouth-0.8.3-r4.ebuild:
  0.8.3-r4:
  - libdrm_intel, libdrm_nouveau and libdrm_radeon are optional and controlled
    by USE flags (Lucian Muresan)
  - branding (Favero Francesco)
  - initd script (Favero Francesco, but slightly modified)
  - dropped dracut dependency (it's not required)
  - mounting /boot is not necessary
  - works with libpng-1.4.x
  - static libraries are disabled
  - *.la files handled by autotools-utils eclass
  - EAPI changed to 3
  - more informative postint message

  0.8.3-r3:
  - cosmetic changes

  See bug #274065[0] for details.  Thanks to all contributors.

  [0] https://bugs.gentoo.org/show_bug.cgi?id=274065

*plymouth-0.8.3-r3 (16 Aug 2010)

  16 Aug 2010; Amadeusz Żołnowski <aidecoe@aidecoe.org>
  +plymouth-0.8.3-r3.ebuild, -plymouth-0.8.3-r2.ebuild:
  Ebuild from bug #274065.  0.8.3-r3 fixes QA warnings.  Removed ebuild with QA
  warnings.

*plymouth-0.8.3-r2 (16 Aug 2010)

  16 Aug 2010; Amadeusz Żołnowski <aidecoe@aidecoe.org> +metadata.xml,
  +plymouth-0.8.3-r2.ebuild, +files/0.8.3-gentoo-fb.patch:
